contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|DS|Ds|dS|ds}} '''DS''' may refer to: {{tocright}} ==Entertainment== * [[Dead Space (video game)]], third person horror video game * [[Deca Sports]], sports video game for the Nintendo Wii developed by Hudson Soft * [[Nintendo DS]], a hand held gaming device made by Nintendo * [[Double Spoiler]], the 12.5th game in the [[Touhou Project]] series. ==Geography== * [[Dunajská Streda]], a town in Slovakia ==Mathematics & science== * dS, an abbreviation for [[dwarf spiral galaxy]] * [[Darmstadtium]], a chemical element with atomic number 110 * [[Dielectric spectroscopy]], or Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy, measures dielectric properties of medium as function of frequency * [[Directional symmetry]], a method for time series analysis * [[DS register]], or data segment register, of X86 computer architecture * [[Dry matter|Dry solids]] ==Organizations== *[[Bureau of Diplomatic Security]], in the United States Department of State *[[Democrats of the Left|Democratici di Sinistra]], (Democrats of the Left), a former Italian political party *[[Democratic Party (Serbia)|Demokratska stranka]], (Democratic Party), a Serbian political party *[[Committee for State Security|Darzhavna sigurnost]], (State Security), a former Bulgarian secret service *[[Divisional Secretariats of Sri Lanka]] ==Medicine== *[[Down syndrome]], a medical condition *[[Duodenal switch]], short for Bilio-Pancreatic Diversion with Duodenal Switch ==Music== *[[D.S. (song)|"D.S." (song)]], a 1995 song by Michael Jackson *[[Derek Sherinian]] (born 1966), keyboardist *[[Dal Segno]], a navigation marker in music notation ==Technology== *[[Avid DS]], an Avid Technology High-Resolution editing and effects application *Distribution System, most commonly referring to [[Wireless Distribution System|WDS]] *[[Directory service]], a software system that stores, organizes and provides access to information in a directory *[[DirectShow]], a multimedia framework and API produced by Microsoft *Delegation Signer, a new record type defined within [[DNSSEC]] *Draft Standard, a maturity level of an [[Internet standard]] the ds has a game slot ==Theology== *[[Enchiridion symbolorum, definitionum et declarationum de rebus fidei et morum]], a compendium of all basic texts of Catholic dogma, abbreviated DS <!-- in catechetics for "Denzinger-Schönmetzer," the names of its initial compiler and a later editor--> ==Military== *[[DS-39]], '''D'''egtyaryova '''S'''tankovyi Model 1939, a Russian medium machine gun ==Other uses== *[[7.92 DS]], a Polish-designed anti-tank ammunition type *[[EasyJet Switzerland]] (IATA code) *[[Citroën DS]], a model of Citroën car *[[DS car marque]], the new upmarket marque or brand set up by Citroën to run alongside its mainstream cars *[[Dead space (physiology)]], air that is inhaled by the body in breathing, but does not partake in gas exchange *Detective Sergeant, a rank within the British [[Criminal Investigation Department]] *Detective [[Superintendent (police)]], a rank used by British police *D/s, short for [[dominance and submission]] *D/s, Down Stream *[[Dnepropetrovsk Sputnik]], a type of soviet satellites ==See also== *[[Dis (disambiguation)]] {{disambiguation}}
